 In a statement to newsrooms, the Foreign Affairs Ministry said the two leaders held discussions on the strengthening of bilateral ties between Kenya and China. "...the meeting lauded the strong bilateral relations between Kenya and People’s Republic of China noting that it has been elevated to strategic cooperation under the stewardship of the two Heads of State," reads the statement. The Special Envoy informed the Cabinet Secretary that he had the opportunity of visiting some of the infrastructural projects undertaken by the Chinese Government like the Nairobi Expressway which is a tangible manifestation of the strong ties." The meeting also reviewed the security situation in the Horn of Africa. "The Cabinet Secretary appreciated China’s efforts in contributing to peace and development in the region. The Special Envoy on his part informed that the purpose of his visit was to consolidate the facts on the situation in the Horn of Africa in relation to peace and development," added the statement. The two leaders also discussed the need to infuse the climate change aspect into peace and stability engagements in order to build resilience and adaptability among communities. CS Omamo also rooted for the inclusion of Women and the youth in the discussion of peace and development in the region.